        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 7:03PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 701 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 9 miles east of
Madisonville to 9 miles southwest of Bedias to near College Station.
Movement was southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
College Station, Bryan, northwestern Huntsville, Navasota,
Madisonville, Bedias, Kurten, Wixon Valley, Millican, Anderson, Kyle
Field, Iola, Crabbs Prairie, Wellborn, Roans Prairie, Richards, and
Carlos.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
southeastern Texas.</instruction>
